Help page for slko Makefile:
1) Use "make all" to build the kernel module and tools for configuring it.
2) Use "make clean" to remove all files generated by Kbuild exclude final build of this kernel module.
3) Use "make remove_build" to remove kernel module and tools for configuring it.
4) Use "make load/unload" to load/unload kernel module
5) Use "make help" to show this message

[SCHEME OF SLKO KERNEL MODULE'S INFRASTRUCTURE]
/lib/modules/
    |slko/
        |slko.ko
        |slko_settings/
            |slko_settings <- binary have symlink /usr/bin/slko_settings
            |slko.conf <- config file that will be parsed via "make load"

